Stir the flour, cornmeal, sugar and salt together in a medium mixing bowl. Mix the eggs and LACTAID(R) Reduced Fat Milk. Combine with the flour mixture, and mix with a wire whisk until smooth. Heat about 1 tablespoon of oil in a large saute pan or skillet over medium-high heat. Cook Johnny cakes. Drop about 2 tablespoons of batter for each Johnny Cake on the griddle. Cook 1 to 2 minutes on each side, or until the edges begin to bubble. Flip and cook until golden. Serve warm on a large platter with your choice of accompaniments.